Author: designer#4893
Content:
the essence of money is versatile. If the ecosystem is valuable, general currency is used. It is no use restricting official currency to tokens. That is, any payment method recognized outside the ecosystem can be used. That is also the definition of a valuable ecosystem. 

If the token, which is made of ICO, is universal, it is also used in other ecosystems.

But ICO tries to resemble mileage and falls into a more serious logical leap than economists who explain money, and is going to go on about it. If a worthless ecosystem recognizes an unqualified token as an official currency, it is close to claiming that the ecosystem is worthwhile and the token is money.

The real reason why many ICO are blocking in front of regulation may be hidden by the intellectual frailties of those who try ICO, the lack of reflection, and the belief in superstitious logic rather than the will of the regulatory authorities.

Bitcoin, which marks the 10th anniversary of its birth, is demanding a humble reflection on the nature of this phenomenon. No, forcing you.

Author: Acura#2748
Content:
I'd be very careful about that.

Looks like scam to me. No team on the website, WP is throwing a few buzzwords around without explaining how they want to implement what, github Repo doesn't have its own code yet, and (worst of all): how are users supposed to get their WavesX tokens? Sure, they log on to the WavesX Wallet, the mapping from the original Waves address to the Waves X address (where the tokens are located), but can only be done via the seed. I wouldn't enter my seed there...
